 Mthatha - Mthatha Vispol members were conducting patrols when they received an information about a man selling dagga at the Walter Sisulu University campus on Tuesday, at about 23h00. "They arrested a 42-year-old man, who is not a student at the university," said police spokesperson, Captain Dineo Koena. "He was found in possession of dagga weighing 5,628kg with the street value of R5 628 and R1 245.10 in cash." She said that the man will appear before Mthatha Magistrate's Court on Wednesday for delaing in dagga. Follow more RNEWS articles, subscribe to our YouTube channel and for breaking news LIKE us on Facebook. For news on the Western Cape click here. For great savings on life’s little pleasures visit Bargain Buys!  Know somebody who is getting married, Wedding and Function can assist.  Have kids, then you need to visit Kids Connection. Enjoy food and travel, then visit Home Food and Travel. Need assistance with an online presence, visit Agency One. 